Description: Jar of marl pottery with small flat base and narrow convex sides, high shoulder, inset neck with rounded and everted rim. Two short wavy-handles are applied below the shoulder.
Curator's comments: Shape like Wavy handled W37 in Petrie’s Corpus of Prehistoric Pottery (1921).
Condition: fair; Rim chipped, some accretions on surface.
Acquisition name: Purchased through: R J Moss & Co
